text.tspan: UBT1_003141 nitrate reductase molybdenum cofactor assembly chaperone [Carbonactinospora thermoautotrophica]
nitrate reductase molybdenum cofactor assembly chaperone similar to Escherichia coli Redox enzyme maturation protein NarW that is
required for proper molybdenum cofactor insertion and final assembly of the membrane-bound respiratory nitrate reductase 2
UBT1_003142 nitrate reductase subunit beta [Carbonactinospora thermoautotrophica]
nitrate reductase subunit beta is a component of nitrate reductase enzyme complex that allows bacteria to use nitrate as an electron
UBT1_003140 respiratory nitrate reductase subunit gamma [Carbonactinospora thermoautotrophica]
respiratory nitrate reductase subunit gamma is part of the enzyme complex (composed of alpha, beta and gamma subunits) that allows
the use of nitrate as an electron acceptor during anaerobic growth; the gamma chain is a membrane-embedded heme-iron unit resembling cytochrome b, which
transfers electrons from quinones to the beta subunit
UBT1_003143 nitrate reductase subunit alpha [Carbonactinospora thermoautotrophica]
nitrate reductase subunit alpha (NarG) is part of the nitrate reductase complex, which uses nitrate as an electron acceptor during
anaerobic growth. The complex contains the catalytic subunits alpha and beta, as well as two gamma subunits, which are responsible for membrane attachment.
IKOGDBKN_03593; Assimilatory nitrate reductase catalytic subunit
molybdopterin oxidoreductase family protein similar to Bacillus subtilis formate dehydrogenase YrhE and oxidoreductase YjgC
